&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available to join the team on the Rushmere Medical Day Unit based at Ipswich Hospital.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a motivated and enthusiastic individual who is able to help lead the team. Rushmere Medical day unit is an elective care setting treating patients from all specialties, currently treating up to 30 patients per day. Such procedures undertaken on the unit include a variety of infusions, Endocrine tests, biopsies, chest drains, Picc line insertions, Paracentesis, Lumbar punctures, Transesophageal echocardiograms and Venesections. The unit is open Monday to Friday 08.00 - 20.00&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicant will become a part of the Rushmere management team overseeing the Day unit/OPAT/PICC service and cardiology lists. You will gain knowledge on all management duties which can help you gain experience towards a band 7 role. You will also have the opportunity to assist in the implementation of new services and to assist in the development of new patient pathways.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gemma Austin or Laura Brock, Ward Sister - gemma.austin@esneft.nhs.uk or laura.brock@esneft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
